# MULTI-PLATFORM RULES
- All platform-specific code goes through IPlatformService interface
- Use #if UNITY_WEBGL / #if UNITY_ANDROID / #if UNITY_IOS ONLY inside Platform/ folder
- PlatformBootstrap selects implementation at startup → ServiceLocator.Register
- Game logic (Core/), UI, Gameplay, Networking — NEVER contain platform #if directives
- Networking uses IWebSocketTransport abstraction (WebGL=jslib, native=ClientWebSocket)
- MVP implements WebGLPlatform + EditorPlatform only

# WEBGL CONSTRAINTS (applies to WebGL build)
- No System.Threading (use coroutines)
- No File I/O (use PlayerPrefs or server API)
- No System.Net.Sockets (use jslib WebSocket interop)
- Minimize garbage allocation (object pooling, avoid LINQ in hot paths)
- Target 60fps on mobile browsers
- Bundle size matters — no unnecessary packages
- Build settings: IL2CPP OptimizeSize, High Stripping, Brotli, ASTC, WASM 2023

# DETERMINISM RULES
- ActionResolver and all game systems must be deterministic
- Same inputs → same outputs on any platform
- No Random (use seeded if needed), no float math in logic, no Dictionary order dependency
- No string.GetHashCode() for gameplay — use SHA256
- C# and TypeScript implementations must produce identical results

# WHAT TO AVOID
- Do NOT use Update() for game logic — use event-driven architecture
- Do NOT use FindObjectOfType or GameObject.Find — use DI or SerializeField
- Do NOT allocate in hot paths (ToString, string concat, LINQ in Update)
- Do NOT use physics engine for grid movement — use pure grid math
- Do NOT hardcode hero stats — always reference ScriptableObjects
- Do NOT use Camera.main (cache it)
- Do NOT use Resources.Load (use direct references)
- Do NOT put game logic in MonoBehaviours — Core layer only
- Do NOT access View layer from Network layer — use GameEvents
